Description:
PRICE REDUCTION!
Situated in a quiet pocket on the East Melbourne fringe, this contemporary apartment is only moments from Melbourne's cultural hub.
The light-filled residence comprises spacious open plan living and dining area, 2 generous bedrooms with built-in robes, stylish gourmet kitchen with stone benchtops and a sparkling central bathroom with laundry facilities. A prized north facing balcony bathes in natural light. Secure off street parking plus loads of storage.
Within easy reach of the CBD and the vibrant art, dining and entertainment precincts of Smith and Brunswick Streets & a short stroll to the CBD. Ideal for first home buyers and investors.

Description:
FEATURE-PACKED HOME ON THE CITY'S DOORSTEP!
More than meets the eye, this handsome freestanding 3BR period home delivers a fabulously versatile city-edge lifestyle making it an ideal investment or first-home opportunity. Situated on a generous corner allotment, the homes surprisingly spacious interior features two large downstairs bedrooms, master ensuite and main bathroom, big lounge/dining through to the updated kitchen and adjoining meals area. Upstairs: flexible second living/study area and third bedroom complete with its own ensuite bathroom. Other highlights include gas heating and split-system a/c, alarm, plus a delightful brick-paved courtyard garden and side driveway to carport (dual off-street parking). A ready-to-enjoy package with options to further enhance, located in a dynamic Collingwood neighbourhood close to Smith Street shops and restaurants, an abundance of local cafs and public transport options to the CBD.
Agent: Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd

Description:
Perfect first home or investment
Located in Collingwood on the corner of Wellington and Hotham Street is this highly-desirable apartment enjoying a superbly convenient position with the area’s best restaurants and bars just seconds away. The inside living spaces are well thought out and more like a house than a unit with a good sized kitchen meals, separate lounge room with heating, ceiling fan and automatic window shutter, huge main bedroom with built-in robe, spacious bathroom and off-street parking. Moments from Vibrant Smith and Brunswick Street and so close to the City makes this a must see.
For further information or to arrange an inspection contact Domenic Mafodda on 0403276856

Description:
MAKING THE DECISION EASY
Fresh, with bold clean lines this architect designed apartment will suit those with the vitality to seek the excitement of city life. Styled for comfort and hassle free living, close to shops, restaurants, nightlife location and on the verge of the CBD this property represents a superb investment opportunity as it is offered subject to the current lease or it could be the ideal city home. There are two generous bedrooms, (BIRs), a tasteful hotel fashioned bathroom and internal laundry. Floor to ceiling windows line the fabulous living area and invite in a sea of green from the mature street trees. Opening onto a private balcony the apartment has an alfresco feel yet is also cosy. A well appointed kitchen completes the lifestyle package. Features include security entrance, central heating, extra storage cupboards and easily accessed lock up garage. A must see for those wishing to secure a piece of city convenience.

A POT OF GOLD
There’s no better time than now to enter into the property market with this tastefully refurbished ground floor apartment in a prime location. Offering security entrance, open plan living with polished floorboards, master bedroom with built in robes and the ensuite bathroom has the added convenience of laundry facilities. Description:
VICTORIAN INTO CONTEMPORARY CLEAN-EDGED URBAN STYLE
This immaculate terrace, light-filled and designed for low maintenance living, is the ideal first home in this popular location close to cafes, transport and Smith street restaurant precinct. Set behind a private walled courtyard, it opens to an arched hallway leading to two double bedrooms and a neat tiled bathroom. The kitchen equipped with smart cabinetry, stainless steel range and laundry plumbing is open to a large sunny living and dining area flowing through a wall of glass to a north-facing decked courtyard, fitted with gas BBQ and storage (pedestrian ROW access). This appealing property features period plasterwork, Tasmanian oak floors, quality carpets and split-system air conditioning. Its a delight!

Description:
SPACE, POTENTIAL AND A GREAT LOCATION!
This substantial Victorian in sound refurbished condition offers wonderful scope for extension and further renovation (STCA), in a tree-lined street close to Queens Parade, cafes, train and tram transport, and within the Gold Street Primary zone. Entry from the verandah is to an arched hallway opening to a spacious bedroom with deep cornices and an open fireplace. In the centre of the house is an expansive living and dining room, open through a cut out wall to a neat modern kitchen with access to the back garden. Also on the lower level is a sunny bathroom with over bath shower. Two very large upstairs bedrooms, one with treetop views to the CBD, have open fireplaces and storage space. The deep brick-paved and landscaped rear garden contains an external laundry. This inviting residence features good period detail, understair storage, parquetry floors and reverse-cycle air conditioning.

Description:
Embrace An Exciting Life On The Edge
Stylish, contemporary and delightfully peaceful inside, you may find it hard to believe that this brilliantly positioned one bedroom plus study apartment is just moments from lively Smith Street, vibrant Brunswick Street and so close to the CBD.
The central living/meals/kitchen boasts a host of quality Bosch appliances, stone counters and access to a private balcony.
The bedroom features mirrored built-in robes, and the study is a welcome feature.
You will also find a chic bathroom plus a European laundry with washer/dryer, secure intercom entry, reverse cycle heating/cooling, a storage cage and secure undercover parking.
Stroll to excellent restaurants, cafes, shops, parks, trams and trains.
ACU, NMIT and hospitals are also nearby, adding appeal for students and medical professionals.

Description:
"Super-Central"
With a super-central position on the hub of Abbottsford, Collingwood and East Melbourne, you'll be like a kid in a candy store with all of the delights. The amazing Victoria Street food, relaxed bars and colourful Collingwood culture just keep getting better & with public transport, the MCG & the CBD all within reach, life can be a whole lot easier here at "The Islington".
With large proportions in all rooms & a big balcony overlooking a large mature courtyard, there's no reason for you not to get down here and snap this up, whether you're entering the market or just looking for a great return in the city fringe.
Consisting of:
- Spacious 2 bedroom N/E facing apartment
- Elevated balcony with garden outlook
- Very large bedrooms with built-in robes
- Huge open plan kitchen/dining/living
- Large central bathroom with laundry
- One secure undercover car space on title
- Modern kitchen with gas cooking
- Courtyard aspect at the rear of the block
- Ample storage throughout
- Two reverse cycle A/C + heating units
- Dual access to secure parking
- Access from Hoddle Street & Islington Street
- Public transport on the door: Train, Tram and Bus.
- Location, Location, Location
- Hurry!

Description:
ELEGANT DESIGN,SUPERB OUTDOOR LIVING!
This ultra-spacious three bedroom town residence, just minutes from East Melbourne parks, the MCG, Smith Street and Victoria Street restaurants, offers exceptional outdoor entertaining areas - a landscaped garden, large balcony, and roof terrace with stunning city views. Entry from the delightful front garden is to a good-sized home office, equipped with home theatre facilities, adjoining a remote entry double garage and separate laundry. Three spacious bedrooms and a bathroom occupy the middle level; the main bedroom includes a walk-in wardrobe and a stylish ensuite bathroom. Floored in mellow hardwood, the living and dining area flows out to a north-facing balcony overlooking the garden. To one side of this expansive entertaining area, the timber-finished kitchen features Blanco appliances and stone bench tops. On the upper level, the roof top deck provides panoramic CBD and northerly views.
This surprisingly quiet light-filled low maintenance property, finished to the highest standards, features generous storage, ducted heating and cooling, video entry, alarm system and premium fittings. It's a must-see!
Agent: Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd
